# Force LF line endings for shell scripts so Git Bash on Windows (which respects
# core.autocrlf) doesn't reintroduce CRLF on checkout. CRLF in a .sh file makes the
# shebang `#!/bin/bash\r` and the kernel reports "no such file or directory" for
# `/bin/bash\r` — which is what bricked the Scylla startup container.
*.sh text eol=lf
